Commit: Integration of HIV/AIDS Drug Discovery Datasets and Front-End Setup for Data Science Pipeline

Overview:
This commit integrates multiple HIV/AIDS drug discovery datasets into a scalable data science workflow and marks the beginning of front-end development. The datasets provide chemical, pharmacological, and patent information suitable for machine learning, predictive modelling, and analytics. The front-end setup will allow visualization, interactive exploration, and user-friendly access to the integrated data.

Data Sources:

ChEMBL Compound Data – CHEMBL114
https://www.ebi.ac.uk/chembl/explore/compound/CHEMBL114
Provides curated bioactivity data for CHEMBL114
Includes chemical structures, targets, assays, and activity metrics
Suitable for feature engineering and predictive modelling

PubChem HIV/AIDS Drug Discovery Datasets
https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/#query=drug+discovery+related+HIV+AIDS+datasets
Structured chemical and biological datasets relevant to HIV/AIDS
Ready for ML tasks (classification/regression)
Supports batch downloads and integration into Python/R pipelines

WIPO Patent Data – WO2025125695
https://patentscope.wipo.int/search/en/detail.jsf?docId=WO2025125695
Includes chemical structures, claims, and synthesis methods
Useful for patent analytics and NLP-based text mining pipelines

DrugBank Compound DB15656
https://go.drugbank.com/drugs/DB15656
Pharmacological and chemical data for HIV/AIDS-related compounds
Supports ML pipelines for drug–target interaction prediction

DrugBank Compound DB11066
https://go.drugbank.com/drugs/DB11066
Detailed chemical, clinical, and interaction data
Supports drug repurposing studies and predictive analytics

Technical Integration:

API-based ingestion of ChEMBL and DrugBank datasets
Batch download and preprocessing of PubChem structured datasets
Parsing chemical and bioactivity features for machine learning
Integration of patent metadata for NLP-based analytics
Data cleaning, normalization, feature engineering, and dataset merging
Front-end development initiated – adding initial files for data visualization and user interface

Intended Applications:

Predictive modelling for HIV/AIDS drug activity or classification
Drug–target interaction analysis using supervised and unsupervised methods
Patent-informed novelty detection and analytics
Interactive data visualization and exploration through the front-end
Support for end-to-end data science workflows with Python, Spark, or cloud pipelines

Significance:

This integration establishes a unified dataset combining chemical, pharmacological, and patent information while initiating front-end development for interactive exploration. It enables robust data science pipelines, supports ML-driven drug discovery workflows, and facilitates reproducible analytics for research and development in HIV/AIDS therapeutics.

